A unique "electronic goods ticket" for return goods Setouchi City is added to the hometown tax: Sanyo Newspaper Digital | San Diego
"E Street Gift."
to make contact with the dedicated equipment
Setonai City announced on July 27 that it would add its own electronic ticket "e-machi Gift" to the return goods of the hometown tax.
It is available in the city's affiliated stores from November.
It was the first municipality in the prefecture.
If you pay Furusato tax and choose an electronic ticket as a reward, 30% of the donation will be sent to the designated smartphone.
When purchasing a product, it shows the screen of the product ticket, and the store contacts the stamp-type dedicated equipment and settles it.
They cannot be sold or sold.
Recipients usually require a certain amount of time from application to arrival, but electronic ticketing can be received instantly.
Tourists are easily available.
In addition to the five Hometown Tax Portals, two special sites in the city are also accepted.
The company currently operates 13 stores, with a target of 100 by the end of this fiscal year.
In June, the Ministry of Internal Affairs and Communications established a new system to regulate local products in order to prevent excessive competition between municipalities, with the amount of return goods raised to less than 30% of the donation amount.
The city has stated that "it is planned to be a member of a local product company and within the guidelines."
In the 18th year of Setouchi City, the amount of hometown tax is about 430 million yen.
