Driving in high heels is dangerous!
Accidents involving the wrong pedal of young people - Yahoo!
Violations against Road Traffic Law
The number of reports on accidents caused by mishandling such as pedal treading is increasing, but it is a big mistake to think that this is a problem only for elderly drivers.
According to the 2015 National Police Agency data, more than 1080 people aged 24 or younger were killed, surpassing 1032 people aged 75 or older.
It is important to call attention to the younger generation as well.
will you take your feet?
is it safe?
There is no description of the gender ratio or cause of this data, but unlike the elderly who are often thought to be due to the decline of the body, such as driving skills and reflexes, in the younger generation, it is possible to take steps due to accidental mistakes due to other things such as music and conversation, etc.
In particular, women choose a variety of shoes depending on the clothes of the day, such as high heels, pamps, sandals, and mulles.
Some people say it is troublesome to change clothes while knowing that it is not suitable for driving, but some people do not think about the possibility that it will lead to danger at all, and many people drive without hesitation.
However, driving in high heels and sandals violates road traffic laws.
The first is to ensure that the steering wheel, brakes and other operations are operated. Article 70 of the Act stipulates that "the operation should not be operated to cause accidents and harm to people."
The other is Article 71, which stipulates that drivers must comply with the matters stipulated by the prefectural public safety committees, for example, in Article 12 of the Enforcement Regulations of the Miyazaki Prefectural Road Traffic Law, for example, "Do not drive vehicles (except light vehicles) by wearing shoes in a manner that prevents driving operations, or by wearing shoes that may interfere with driving operations, such as slippers, suspensions, high heels, etc."
It is similar to the intention of each prefecture to consider the operation as a violation of " footwear that can prevent operation" even if it is not specified as high heels.
So why is driving at high heels dangerous?
It is obvious considering the basics of safely pedaling.
For safe and secure pedal operation, first place the feet to be perpendicular to the brake pedal, and when stepping on the accelerator pedal, tilt the feet to the right as the starting point.
At this time, regardless of the behavior of the car, it is important to keep it firmly fixed so that it does not break.
However, in high heels, the area where the kato is grounded on the floor is small, and the area where the kato is grounded on the pedal is always blur, and because the height of the heel is angled throughout the foot, the area of the foot that is grounded on the pedal is also smaller, and it is difficult to make fine adjustments.
This may lead to danger.
In addition, most cars have floor carpets, but this material is easy to catch a high heel, and sometimes when it comes to sudden braking, the heel is pulled and the pedal cannot be stepped, or the high heel is removed from the time signature when the heel is pulled, and it can not be stepped inside the pedal.
In addition, there is a case where the heel pulls to the back side of the pedal when stepping back from the pedal, and the accelerator pedal disappears.
Toyota and Subaru to Accelerate Joint Development (Response) - Yahoo!News
Toyota and Subaru agreed to a new business capital alliance on September 27.
Toyota will acquire Subaru shares and become an affiliate of the equity method.
Since the agreement in 2005, the two companies have been working together to produce Toyota vehicles commissioned by Subaru, supply vehicles from Toyota to Subaru, and joint development of the FR sports car "86."
In June of this year, we agreed to develop EV-only platforms and EV vehicles using Subaru's All-wheel drive technology and Toyota's electrification technology.
In this agreement, Toyota will acquire additional Subaru shares.
At present, Toyota's shares held by Subaru are 16.83% voting rights, but they are acquired until they reach 20%.
Subaru is an affiliate of Toyota's equity method.
On the other hand, Subaru will acquire Toyota shares equivalent to the same amount (up to 8 billion yen) as the amount required to acquire Subaru shares.
Both companies develop and strengthen cooperative relationships through business capital alliances.
Joint development of the AWD and 86/BRZ models, expansion of the THS (Toyota Hybrid System) to Subaru vehicles, coordination in the connected area, technical cooperation in the autonomous driving field, etc.
U.S., at least 18,000 people in three consecutive years | Shizuoka Shimbun
The U.S. Department of State announced on October 26, 2020 that it will reduce the number of refugees accepted from around the world to 18,000.
The minimum number of refugees since 1980 has been renewed for three consecutive years.
The Trump administration aims to appeal to the conservatives the strict immigration and refugee policies following the next presidential election.
It is inevitable that people who are driven out of the country in various places will be criticized by human rights organizations.
The previous Obama administration set the limit to 110,000 in fiscal 2017, but the Trump administration, which was inaugurated in January 1717, overturned it and reduced it to 50,000.
It has been reduced to 45,000 in fiscal 2006 and 30,000 in fiscal 2007.
