Korea-Bulgarian Summit on Cooperation in Nuclear Power Plants and Defense Industries (Bulgarians) | Yahoo!
(SEOUL=Yonhap News) South Korea's President Moon Jae-in met with Bulgaria's Prime Minister Borisov during his official visit to Korea and discussed ways to expand bilateral cooperation.
This is the first time the Prime Minister of Bulgaria visited Korea.
President Moon welcomed the visit to Korea prior to the 30th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic relations next year and appreciated the leadership of Prime Minister Borisov, leading the development of Bulgaria.
The two leaders appreciated the continued increase in trade and investment between the two countries amid the growing global protectionist tradeism and agreed to work together to expand economic cooperation in the future.
President Moon welcomed Bulgaria's policy of granting Korean companies the status of "strategic investors" and said that he hoped that Korean companies would promote investment in Bulgaria based on this.
He also stressed that while Bulgaria is promoting the introduction of nuclear power plants and the modernization of national defense, Korea will be the best partner for Bulgaria. He called for attention and cooperation so that Korean companies can participate in the order of the Bulgarian government's nuclear power plants and the promotion of the defense industry.
In addition, the two leaders agreed to strengthen future-oriented cooperation in the areas of battery and auto parts for electric vehicles and renewable energy.
Prime Minister Borisov hoped that close cooperation between ICT (Information and Communication Technology) and science and technology, as well as education, would be possible.
The Peace Process on the Korean Peninsula was also discussed, and President Moon expressed his gratitude for the support of the Korean government's efforts to establish peace on the Korean Peninsula, including the announcement of a statement by Bulgaria that supports the North-South and North-South summits.
Prime Minister Borisov appreciated President Moon's will to build a peace regime on the Korean Peninsula and the efforts of the Korean government.
The meeting was attended by Secretary of the Ministry of Trade, Industry and Energy Sung Yunmo, Chief Secretary of the Economic Affairs of Chong Chong (President's Office), Kim Hyun-jong, Second Director of the State Security Office.
As deputy director of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Kang Gyeong-wa (Kang Gyeong-fa) visited the United States, the first official of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Zhao Seong, also attended.
Local industry in Hyogo and Awaji Island, Kinki Ceramics, manufactured by Awaji Kawara, filed for quasi-self-insolvency debt of approximately 2 billion yen (Imperial Data Bank) - Yahoo!
It was also affected by the sluggish housing market and the progress of "consumer roofing away" due to the frequent earthquake damage.
Kinki Ceramics Co., Ltd. (TDB Corporation Code: 530173983, capital of 99.9 million yen, 881-8 Otani, Awaji City, Hyogo Prefecture, representative Yukizo Fukuhara, and 44 employees) filed for quasi-self-insolvency at the Kobe District Court on August 30.
The applicant is Daichi Yoshida (1-10-8 Nishitenman, Kita Ward, Osaka City, Osaka Prefecture), Daichi Yoshida Law Office, and telephone number 06-665-6038.
The company was founded in June 1895 and reorganized in April 1961.
At first, he started his business as a Ibushi tile maker in Nishitan-cho, Mihara County (now Minamiawaji City) under the trade name of Kinki Kiln Co., Ltd.
In October 1986, Kyowa Kiln Co., Ltd. merged into Kyowa Kiln Co., Ltd. and succeeded the business of Kinki Sangyo Co., Ltd., but at the same time, the head office was relocated to its present location after the change to the current business name.
After that, sales offices were established in Fukuyama City, Hiroshima City, Oita City, Miyazaki City, etc. to become the current system, and Juzen mainly used Ibushi tiles, but due to changes in consumer demand, Western-style tiles such as flat plate tiles were manufactured at a rate of 70 percent and 30% of Japanese-style tiles such as Ibushi tiles.
The company has established a wide range of sales bases in western Japan, including major house manufacturers, construction materials trading companies, and roof construction companies.
He was well known as the top tile maker of Awaji Island.
However, due to the sluggish housing market following the Lehman shock and the frequent damage from the Great East Japan Earthquake and the Kumamoto Earthquake, demand for tiled roofs has been sluggish, and annual sales for the fiscal year ended December 2018 were down to approximately 1345 million yen.
In terms of profits, in addition to the decline in the profit margin due to the surge in fuel prices, the company suffered a continuous deficit due to excessive interest-bearing debt associated with inventory burdens and business fixed investment, and was forced to make severe financing.
For this reason, the Bank tried to rebuild its business by requesting financial institutions to ease the conditions for repayment of loans, but there was no sign of a recovery in business conditions, and gradually the financial position was imminent.
He was unable to support the project and gave up his business continuity.
The debt is currently under investigation, but is expected to be about 2 billion yen.
The Prefectural Dinosaur Museum, located in Katsuyama City, Fukui Prefecture, is promoting "industrialization of tourism."
Katsuyama City, Fukui Prefecture, announced on September 25 that it will acquire approximately 25,000 square meters of land adjacent to the construction site of the road station "Dinosaur Valley Katsuyama," which will open next spring.
In order to accelerate the "industrialization of tourism" advocated by the city and local economy, we aim to attract accommodation-specific hotels and restaurants.
A member of the board of directors explained the same day at the Special Committee on the Improvement of the City Council's Invitational Base.
In addition to opening the Hokuriku Shinkansen line in the spring of 2023, the entire section of the Chubu Ritsukan Expressway will be opened, and the prefectural Dinosaur Museum (Katsuyama City) will be renovated and enhanced.
It is a private idle land next to the road station construction site east.
Surrounded by the Kuzuryu River, Takinami River, and prefectural roads, the station is more than twice the size of a road station (about 12,000 square meters).
Under the name of the industrial complex, the City Land Development Corporation will proceed with land negotiations from this fiscal year, acquire land, and build land in FY21.
According to the city, private businesses such as farmers' restaurants and harvest experience facilities, fast food, and restaurants have already started business.
As for accommodation, it was revealed that Sekisui House has promoted its name as a city to attract accommodation-specific hotels adjacent to Michi no Eki, which is planned throughout Japan.
Sekisui House plans to expand into three locations in Fukui Prefecture, but it is said that several other cities will attract and compete.
The city also plans to build a parking lot.
Some members called for speed-up, saying that the maintenance schedule was slow, and others said, "I don't have enough land to sleep."
Mr. Sanekio Mizukami, Deputy Mayor of the City of Katsuyama, expressed his determination to attract hotels and other facilities as a tourism-themed industrial complex.
