BITPoint, which leaked 3 billion yen worth of crypto assets, resumed service (Genfusha Gold Online) - Yahoo!
In July of this year, crypto asset exchanges, which amounted to 3 billion yen such as bitcoin, were leaked illegally.
Bitpoint Japan Co., Ltd., the operator, announced on September 30 that it would resume the service of sending crypto assets.
It is thought that certain points were established, including measures to prevent recurrence.
In July of this year, BITPoint leaked Bitcoin and Ripple.
Bitpoint Japan Co., Ltd., which operates the Crypto Asset Exchange BITPoint, announced on September 27 that it will resume its services for sending crypto assets (remittance) services around 14:00 on September 30.
In addition to dealing with customers who have suffered damage and communicating with the Financial Services Agency, there seems to be a certain point of view, including measures to prevent recurrence, such as management management systems including security aspects.
Bitpoint Japan says, "We will resume our services as soon as possible, with safety as the first priority, and strive to recover the trust of our users."
In July of this year, the exchange encountered a cryptocurrency leak worth 3 billion yen, including Bitcoin and Ripple.
In the subsequent press conference, regarding the continuation of the business, he mentioned that "There is a current account balance of about 30 billion yen even if the compensation amount is deducted."
