It has increased by one to six times compared to 2018 and has increased to 24 locations in Fukui Prefecture by nine compared to last year.
why is it now?
Makoto Yuasa, chairman and social activist of the Kyoto NPO, spoke about the background and significance at a lecture held in Sakai City.
Due to the declining birthrate and aging population, the area became lonely and the shopping district declined.
There was no place for people to meet.
And he said, "We needed a place where people interact with each other.
It is also called "the place of multi-generational exchange" where elderly people participate.
It not only eliminates eating alone, but also helps to support child rearing and improve the health of the elderly.
They cut off the chain of poverty and revitalize the region.
What's important is, "Don't make a child that will be born from it."
There are various places to offer meals every day from January 1 to March 1.
There are a wide variety of venues, from several to hundreds, from private homes to temples.
The atmosphere is getting ready for people who want to do it.
The low threshold is attractive.
However, it is difficult to manage and secure staff.
sometimes we hear issues like a secure management system
