The reason why YouTuber became a full-time employee.
Listen to the president who hired (bizSPA!
9/27 (Fri) 8:47
YouTuber is now very popular with young people.
Although it is not uncommon for companies to use it for advertising their own products, some companies have started a unique system called YouTuber adoption, which they employ as regular employees.
Direct Marketing Mix Inc. (DmMiX) is the main business of CRM (customer relationship management).
What does it mean to adopt YouTuber?
Mr. Yuki Kobayashi, Representative Director of DmMiX and Representative Director of Staff First, a subsidiary that was actually adopted by YouTuber, talked about it.
i want to support young people who do their best with YouTuber.
What is YouTuber adoption in the first place?
Yuki Kobayashi (Kobayashi): Now YouTuber is a longing for many young people.
There are also top rankings in the vocational rankings that elementary school students want to take in the future, and the number of young people aiming for will continue to increase.
Until now, we have adopted and supported young people who are chasing dreams such as bandmen and comedians.
In the same way, it is "Youtuber adoption" to support young people who are chasing their dream of becoming YouTuber.
There is an image that YouTuber is something that individuals voluntarily post videos, but why did you think about hiring?
Kobayashi: While many young people are longing for the profession of YouTuber, there is a reality that most YouTuber is not able to make the profit as expected.
There are many creators who make and post videos while working part-time, and those who do not allow their family to recognize the existence of YouTuber.
In this initiative, we will provide an environment for salary and content creation to the creators we employ.
We will support our activities by supporting the disadvantages of the profession of YouTuber, which at first becomes unstable.
