New charges for mobile phones Price reduction in fair competition: Hokkaido Shimbun
In October, a new fee plan for a mobile phone company was released due to the enforcement of the Telecommunications Business Act.
However, it almost stopped.
Mr. Yoshihide Suga, Chief Cabinet Secretary, said last summer, "There is room to lower the price by about 40 percent."
It is a major factor that Rakuten's full-scale entry into the market has been postponed and the oligarchy of three major companies continues.
It is desirable for consumers to be a fee system that is easy to use by fair competition.
I want to ask for the efforts of the mobile companies.
The amendment prohibits a set discount on terminal charges and communication charges.
Instead of selling the terminal fee, the communication fee was set to increase.
SoftBank and KDDI (au) announced plans to make the terminal a maximum of half the price.
However, both companies have a SIM lock that cannot be used for 100 days.
NTT Docomo makes up to one-third of the terminal fee for subscribers of its own lines.
The three companies continue to "enclosure" to prevent transfers to other companies.
The Ministry of Internal Affairs and Communications announced that it would require immediate termination of SIM locks.
Companies must respond quickly.
Rakuten's postponement was due to the lack of communication networks such as base stations.
It was expected to be an explosive in the price-cutting competition, so it looked like a shoulder strap.
Perhaps it was the sweetness of the outlook.
The timing and prices of full-scale services have not been disclosed.
As a company responsible for social infrastructure, we would like to take responsibility for our business.
This revision of the price was triggered by the remarks of Chief Cabinet Secretary Suga.
Mr. Suga complained about the new charges of the three companies: "I think competition will start from now on, and I don't think it's going to be good."
However, the government-made price reduction does not seem to distort the market and encourage sound competition.
The company should develop customer-oriented competition before it is announced by the government.
The cost system of each company is very complex and it is not easy to compare.
The Consumer Affairs Agency called attention to the fact that there are cases where the consumer's burden exceeds half the amount while the terminal advertises such as "maximum half."
Companies must make careful and easy-to-understand explanations to avoid misunderstandings of users themselves.
Cash card of 3 Shinkin in Mie Prefecture - Ise Shimbun
Three Shinkin Banks in Mie Prefecture (Kuwana Mie Shinkin Bank, Kita-Ise Ueno Shinkin Bank, and Kihoku Shinkin Bank) announced on February 26 that they decided to reduce the maximum amount of withdrawal by cash card to prevent damage to special scams.
For depositors aged 70 or older who have not made a certain amount of withdrawal transactions at ATMs for the past three years, the maximum amount that can be withdrawn by cash card is 500,000 yen.
On October 1, Kuwana Mie Shinkin Bank and Kita-Ise Ueno Shinkin Bank were reduced to Kihoku Shinkin Bank from November 1.
In the prefecture, there are many special fraud cases in which cash cards and PINs are stolen by financial institutions and police officials, etc., and those in the Shinkin Bank "want to protect customers' important deposits in the best possible way."
