The Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare (MHLW) announced on September 26, the first time that 424 hospitals in 1455 public hospitals and public hospitals in Japan, including Nikka, were identified as having poor medical records.
In Fukui Prefecture, the Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare verified the treatment results of 14 public and public hospitals.
⇒ Four hospitals subject to reorganization "Standard Funny"
In order to reduce medical expenses that are expanding due to the aging population, it was necessary to promote reorganization and integration with hospitals in conflict areas.
In October, we requested a full-scale review of reorganization and integration at the target hospital, and we will conclude by September next year.
Although there is no compulsion force, it is expected that the local chiefs and residents will be repulsed due to anxiety that nearby hospitals will disappear.
It was announced at the same meeting.
The total number of hospitals targeted was 29.1 percent, with relatively few beds.
By prefecture, Niigata (53,7%), Hokkaido (48,6%), Miyagi (47,5%), Yamaguchi (46,7%), and Okayama (43,3%) were high.
The number of targets was 54 in Hokkaido, and Okinawa was the only one with zero.
Based on data from FY2017, the Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare investigated 1455 hospitals in public and public hospitals that can respond to "altitude acute phase" for severe patients and "acute phase" for general surgery.
He analyzed nine medical records, including cancer and emergency medical care, and whether competing hospitals were located within 20 minutes by car.
In the case of a hospital subject, it is considered that some of the medical departments will be abolished and transferred to other hospitals.
Medical expenses increased rapidly in 25 years, when all baby boomers were 75 or older.
For this reason, the Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare has set the goal of reducing the number of beds in hospitals to 11.91,000 in 18 years.
Currently, there are many beds in the "high-altitude acute" and "acute" periods where nurses are placed thickly and medical expenses are required, while there is a shortage of rehabilitation services that are highly needed for the elderly.
In order to cope with the aging population, it is necessary not only to reduce the number of beds but also to increase rehabilitation.
With regard to the reorganization and integration of hospitals, each prefecture formulated a "regional medical concept" that defined the number of beds required for 25 years.
It is divided into 339 parts of the country, with local governments and medical officials discussing it, but many local residents and chiefs remain cautious and debates are difficult.
The Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare wants to revitalize the discussion by publishing the names of hospitals with poor results.
Comprehensive drill for disaster prevention such as the assumption of Mt.Komagatake eruption, road etc.
On September 27, a comprehensive disaster prevention drill was held in the forest, Nanae and Kabe-cho in the Toshima-kan.
Approximately 400 people from 20 institutions, including roads and three towns, participated.
The first event since the Hokkaido Komagatake Volcano Disaster Prevention Council formulated an evacuation plan incorporating evacuation routes for residents in August.
It was the first time in 18 years that local residents participated in extensive training.
At 8:45 a.m., Mt.Komake erupted and the mud flow reached the town at the foot of the mountain.
When the eruption alert level was raised to 5 (evacuation), evacuation shelters were opened in forests and Nanae Ryocho, and residents moved by buses and police cars prepared by each town.
