PokeTalk is a portable translation machine that provides free loan to 500 stores in Hamamatsu City.
The Hamamatsu Chamber of Commerce and Industry announced on February 26 that it had completed the installation of 500 portable translation machines at its member offices, including stores in Hamamatsu.
It is the first time in Japan that the translators will be deployed in a concentrated manner in the same area, and attention is paid to whether it will improve the ability to respond to inbound tourists.
The loans included 236 restaurants, 113 retail stores, 17 accommodations, and 134 others.
The municipality accounts for 60% of the population.
The map app "Google Map" started to show where to rent, and the location of "stores for foreign languages" can be seen on the smartphone.
It can be accessed from the site of Lake Hamana Tourism Area.
The free loan of PoketTalk, which corresponds to 74 languages, started in April with the initiative that received the declaration of "the largest inbound support city in Japan Hamamatsu" by nine organizations in the city.
The Chamber purchases 500 units and lends them to small and medium-sized businesses that meet the requirements of obtaining hospitality certification and introducing cashless payments.
The representative of the Chamber of Commerce said, "I want foreign customers to develop new customers while the business environment is severe."
