Yamagata City | Yamagata Shimbun
The bidders for the children's play facilities and the Minaminumabara Elementary School were decided by Yamagata City, which is planning to build a social capital (PFI) system by utilizing private funds.
Image of a children's play facility established in Katatani, Yamagata City
The children's play facility is scheduled to be built on the north side of Yamagata Kuchu in Kataya District, and the site area is approximately 23400 square meters.
The building is a steel building with a total floor area of about 3,000 square meters.
It has a semi-underground gymnasium, café and book corner.
It also features a universal design playground that allows children with disabilities to play outdoors, ensuring 300 parking spaces.
On May 5, a committee meeting was held at the city hall, and 13 shelter groups (Yamagata City) won the bid for 355 million yen including design, opening preparation, maintenance and operation expenses for 15 years.
Design and construction will begin in January next year and will be open in March 2022.
Image of Minaminumabara Elementary School
The school has over 900 children.
It is planned to be built on the north side of the current school building in Iizawa City, with an area of about 25,000 square meters.
It is a three-story reinforced concrete building with a total floor area of 8580 square meters.
There are 30 classrooms, two pools, a steel gymnasium, and a post-school children's club.
At the committee meeting on June 6, the Ichimura Corporation Group (Yamagata City), consisting of eight companies, won the bid for 4.512.1 million yen including design, demolition of the old school building, maintenance and operation expenses for 15 years.
It was designed and built in December and completed in October 22.
